An arctic blast was gathering pace on Monday as plummeting temperatures began to cause problems across the U.S. 

Arctic air was settling into the central states with temperatures expected to be 25 to 45 degrees below average in some places, according to forecasts. 

And with New Year's Eve on Wednesday, weather experts were warning those planning outdoor celebrations to wrap up warmly, as most of the country will experience temperatures below 32F.

